      "content": "interesting. but if the economic impact is such a big part of the debate, doesn't that mean including it as a \"non-negotiable fact\" regarding the benefits kind of overlooks the actual human cost for people who can't just switch to the subway? it seems like a pretty contentious point to call a \"consensus\" if people are literally losing money just to get to work.",
